<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<title>Hunter Rank & Mastery - Untamed</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<nav class="nav">
			<div class="container">
				<a href="/" class="logo">UNTAMED</a>
				<div class="nav-links">
					<a href="/rules">Rules</a>
					<a href="/quick-reference">Quick Reference</a>
					<a href="/character">Characters</a>
					<a href="/bestiary">Bestiary</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</nav>

		<main>
			<div class="container">
				<div class="breadcrumb">
					<a href="/rules">‚Üê Back to Rules</a>
				</div>

				<header class="page-header">
					<h1>Hunter Rank & Mastery</h1>
					<p class="subtitle">Progression Through Experience</p>
				</header>

				<article class="content">
					<div class="intro">
						<p><strong>Untamed has no traditional levels.</strong> Instead, hunters grow through Hunter Rank, stat development, talent unlocks, and weapon mastery earned through real hunts.</p>
					</div>

					<!-- Hunter Rank -->
					<section class="rule-section highlight">
						<h2>Hunter Rank (HR)</h2>
						<p>Hunter Rank measures your progression as a hunter and determines what tier of monsters and gear you can realistically face.</p>
						<p><strong>Starting Rank:</strong> Hunters begin at <strong>HR 0</strong> with access to Tier 1 hunts and gear.</p>

						<h3>HR Tier Bands (Core Progression Table)</h3>
						<table class="progression-table">
							<thead>
								<tr>
									<th>Hunter Rank</th>
									<th>Weapon Tier Unlocks</th>
									<th>Monster Tier Challenges</th>
								</tr>
							</thead>
							<tbody>
								<tr>
									<td>HR 0‚Äì4</td>
									<td>Tier 1 Weapons</td>
									<td>Tier 1 Monsters</td>
								</tr>
								<tr>
									<td>HR 5‚Äì9</td>
									<td>Tier 2 Weapons</td>
									<td>Tier 2 Monsters</td>
								</tr>
								<tr>
									<td>HR 10‚Äì14</td>
									<td>Tier 3 Weapons</td>
									<td>Tier 3 Monsters</td>
								</tr>
								<tr>
									<td>HR 15‚Äì19</td>
									<td>Tier 4 Weapons</td>
									<td>Tier 4 Monsters</td>
								</tr>
								<tr>
									<td>HR 20‚Äì25</td>
									<td>Tier 5 Weapons</td>
									<td>Tier 5 Monsters</td>
								</tr>
								<tr class="legendary">
									<td>HR 26+</td>
									<td>Tier 6+ Weapons</td>
									<td>Legendary & Mythical Hunts</td>
								</tr>
							</tbody>
						</table>
					</section>

					<!-- Milestone Rewards -->
					<section class="rule-section">
						<h2>Getting Stronger (Milestone Rewards)</h2>
						<p>As you gain Hunter Rank, you unlock upgrades at consistent milestones:</p>

						<div class="milestone-grid">
							<div class="milestone-card stats">
								<h3>üìä Stat Growth</h3>
								<p class="milestone-trigger">Every 4 Hunter Ranks</p>
								<p class="milestone-reward">Gain <strong>2 Stat Distribution Points</strong> to customize your character.</p>
							</div>

							<div class="milestone-card talents">
								<h3>‚≠ê Talents</h3>
								<p class="milestone-trigger">Every 5 Hunter Ranks</p>
								<p class="milestone-reward">Choose <strong>1 Talent</strong></p>
								<p class="milestone-note">Talents are small passives or ability upgrades that shape your build.</p>
							</div>

							<div class="milestone-card specs">
								<h3>üéØ Specializations</h3>
								<p class="milestone-trigger">Every 10 Hunter Ranks</p>
								<p class="milestone-reward">Choose <strong>1 Specialization</strong></p>
								<p class="milestone-note">Specializations are bigger changes that push your playstyle into a defined direction (similar to "subclasses," but without classes).</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</section>

					<!-- Rank Advancement -->
					<section class="rule-section highlight">
						<h2>Rank Advancement (CXP & Hunt Milestones)</h2>
						<p><strong>Untamed progression is hunt-driven, not grind-driven.</strong></p>

						<h3>CXP ‚Äì Creature Experience</h3>
						<p>CXP is earned by defeating large, named creatures, representing meaningful combat experience rather than repetitive XP farming.</p>

						<h3>Default Rank Advancement</h3>
						<ul>
							<li><strong>+1 HR</strong> for each successful Large Hunt in your current tier</li>
							<li>A <strong>Wall Hunt</strong> (tier boss):
								<ul>
									<li>gives <strong>+1 HR</strong></li>
									<li>unlocks the next tier</li>
								</ul>
							</li>
							<li><strong>You cannot exceed the top of a band until you clear that tier's Wall Hunt</strong></li>
						</ul>

						<h3>Objective/Ecology Hunts</h3>
						<p>Objective/ecology hunts (rescue, relocate, harvest):</p>
						<ul>
							<li>grant <strong>no HR by default</strong></li>
							<li>grant loot, intel, crafting boons</li>
							<li>GM may award <strong>+1 HR</strong> if the objective hunt meaningfully endangered the party</li>
						</ul>

						<div class="callout">
							<strong>Pacing Example:</strong> HR 1 ‚Üí HR 5 in about 5‚Äì6 hunts (3‚Äì4 Large hunts + the Wall).
						</div>
					</section>

					<!-- Proficiency System -->
					<section class="rule-section">
						<h2>Proficiency System</h2>
						<p>Proficiency represents your training level in skills and weapons.</p>

						<h3>Proficiency Tiers & Bonuses</h3>
						<table class="proficiency-table">
							<thead>
								<tr>
									<th>Proficiency Level</th>
									<th>Bonus</th>
								</tr>
							</thead>
							<tbody>
								<tr>
									<td>Novice</td>
									<td>+0</td>
								</tr>
								<tr>
									<td>Trained</td>
									<td>+2</td>
								</tr>
								<tr class="master">
									<td>Master</td>
									<td>+4</td>
								</tr>
							</tbody>
						</table>

						<h3>How You Become a Master</h3>
						<p>If you gain the same proficiency twice (from Backgrounds, Training, Gear, Talents, etc.), it upgrades to <strong>Master (+4)</strong>.</p>
					</section>

					<!-- Weapon Proficiency -->
					<section class="rule-section highlight">
						<h2>Weapon Proficiency</h2>
						<p>Weapon proficiency is tracked per weapon, and it improves through actual hunts with that weapon.</p>

						<h3>Starting Weapon Proficiency</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>You begin <strong>Trained (+2)</strong> in one weapon of your choice</li>
							<li>All other weapons begin <strong>Novice (+0)</strong></li>
						</ul>

						<h3>Earning Weapon Proficiency (Per Weapon)</h3>
						<table class="proficiency-table">
							<thead>
								<tr>
									<th>Hunts Completed With a Weapon</th>
									<th>Proficiency Level</th>
								</tr>
							</thead>
							<tbody>
								<tr>
									<td>0 Hunts</td>
									<td>Novice (+0)</td>
								</tr>
								<tr>
									<td>5 Hunts</td>
									<td>Trained (+2)</td>
								</tr>
								<tr class="master">
									<td>10 Hunts</td>
									<td>Master (+4)</td>
								</tr>
							</tbody>
						</table>

						<p class="note">This allows multi-weapon mastery over time, but rewards dedication.</p>

						<div class="example-box">
							<h4>Example:</h4>
							<ul>
								<li>Start with Greatsword ‚Üí <strong>Trained (+2)</strong></li>
								<li>Switch to Dual Blades ‚Üí <strong>Novice (+0)</strong></li>
								<li>After 5 successful hunts with Dual Blades ‚Üí <strong>Trained (+2)</strong></li>
								<li>After 10 hunts ‚Üí <strong>Master (+4)</strong></li>
							</ul>
						</div>
					</section>

					<!-- What This Means -->
					<section class="rule-section summary">
						<h2>What This Means in Play</h2>
						<p>Progression in Untamed has four moving parts:</p>

						<div class="progression-pillars">
							<div class="pillar">
								<span class="pillar-number">1</span>
								<h3>Hunter Rank</h3>
								<p>Unlocks stronger tiers of monsters and gear</p>
							</div>

							<div class="pillar">
								<span class="pillar-number">2</span>
								<h3>Stat Points</h3>
								<p>Increase your core abilities every 4 ranks</p>
							</div>

							<div class="pillar">
								<span class="pillar-number">3</span>
								<h3>Talents</h3>
								<p>Provide frequent build-shaping upgrades every 5 ranks</p>
							</div>

							<div class="pillar">
								<span class="pillar-number">4</span>
								<h3>Weapon Proficiency</h3>
								<p>Improves based on hunts completed with each weapon</p>
							</div>
						</div>

						<div class="callout">
							<strong>Your strength comes from experience, mastery, and preparation ‚Äî not generic leveling.</strong>
						</div>
					</section>
				</article>
			</div>
		</main>

		<style>
			* {
				margin: 0;
				padding: 0;
				box-sizing: border-box;
			}

			:root {
				--forest-dark: #1a2e1a;
				--forest-green: #2d5016;
				--moss-green: #4a7c2f;
				--leaf-green: #6b9d3a;
				--amber: #d4a257;
				--earth-brown: #5c4033;
				--cream: #f5f1e8;
				--text-light: #e8e4d8;
			}

			body {
				font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, sans-serif;
				background: var(--forest-dark);
				color: var(--text-light);
				line-height: 1.7;
				min-height: 100vh;
			}

			.container {
				max-width: 900px;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 0 2rem;
			}

			/* Navigation */
			.nav {
				background: var(--forest-green);
				border-bottom: 2px solid var(--amber);
				padding: 1rem 0;
				position: sticky;
				top: 0;
				z-index: 100;
			}

			.nav .container {
				display: flex;
				justify-content: space-between;
				align-items: center;
				max-width: 1200px;
			}

			.logo {
				font-size: 1.5rem;
				font-weight: 900;
				color: var(--amber);
				text-decoration: none;
				letter-spacing: 0.2rem;
			}

			.nav-links {
				display: flex;
				gap: 2rem;
			}

			.nav-links a {
				color: var(--cream);
				text-decoration: none;
				font-weight: 500;
				transition: color 0.3s;
			}

			.nav-links a:hover {
				color: var(--amber);
			}

			/* Breadcrumb */
			.breadcrumb {
				padding: 2rem 0 1rem;
			}

			.breadcrumb a {
				color: var(--leaf-green);
				text-decoration: none;
				font-weight: 500;
			}

			.breadcrumb a:hover {
				color: var(--amber);
			}

			/* Page Header */
			.page-header {
				padding: 2rem 0 3rem;
				text-align: center;
				border-bottom: 2px solid var(--amber);
				margin-bottom: 3rem;
			}

			.page-header h1 {
				font-size: 3rem;
				color: var(--amber);
				margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
			}

			.subtitle {
				font-size: 1.25rem;
				color: var(--leaf-green);
				font-style: italic;
			}

			/* Content */
			.content {
				padding-bottom: 4rem;
			}

			.intro {
				background: var(--moss-green);
				padding: 2rem;
				border-radius: 12px;
				border: 2px solid var(--amber);
				margin-bottom: 3rem;
				font-size: 1.1rem;
			}

			.rule-section {
				background: var(--forest-green);
				padding: 2rem;
				border-radius: 12px;
				margin-bottom: 2rem;
				border: 2px solid var(--earth-brown);
			}

			.rule-section.highlight {
				border-color: var(--amber);
				background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--forest-green) 0%, var(--moss-green) 100%);
			}

			.rule-section.summary {
				border-color: var(--amber);
				border-width: 3px;
			}

			.rule-section h2 {
				color: var(--amber);
				font-size: 1.75rem;
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
			}

			.rule-section h3 {
				color: var(--leaf-green);
				font-size: 1.25rem;
				margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem;
			}

			.rule-section h4 {
				color: var(--amber);
				font-size: 1.1rem;
				margin: 1rem 0 0.5rem;
			}

			.rule-section ul {
				margin-left: 1.5rem;
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
			}

			.rule-section li {
				margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
			}

			/* Tables */
			.progression-table,
			.proficiency-table {
				width: 100%;
				border-collapse: collapse;
				margin: 1.5rem 0;
				background: var(--forest-dark);
				border-radius: 8px;
				overflow: hidden;
			}

			.progression-table th,
			.progression-table td,
			.proficiency-table th,
			.proficiency-table td {
				padding: 1rem;
				text-align: left;
				border-bottom: 1px solid var(--earth-brown);
			}

			.progression-table th,
			.proficiency-table th {
				background: var(--moss-green);
				color: var(--amber);
				font-weight: 600;
			}

			.progression-table tr:last-child td,
			.proficiency-table tr:last-child td {
				border-bottom: none;
			}

			.progression-table tr.legendary,
			.proficiency-table tr.master {
				background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--forest-dark) 0%, var(--moss-green) 100%);
				font-weight: 600;
				color: var(--amber);
			}

			/* Milestone Grid */
			.milestone-grid {
				display: grid;
				grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
				gap: 1.5rem;
				margin: 2rem 0;
			}

			.milestone-card {
				background: var(--forest-dark);
				padding: 2rem;
				border-radius: 12px;
				border: 3px solid var(--leaf-green);
				transition: all 0.3s ease;
			}

			.milestone-card:hover {
				transform: translateY(-4px);
				box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(212, 162, 87, 0.3);
			}

			.milestone-card h3 {
				color: var(--amber);
				font-size: 1.4rem;
				margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
			}

			.milestone-trigger {
				font-weight: 600;
				color: var(--leaf-green);
				margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
				font-size: 1.1rem;
			}

			.milestone-reward {
				margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
			}

			.milestone-note {
				font-style: italic;
				font-size: 0.95rem;
				color: var(--moss-green);
			}

			.milestone-card.stats {
				border-color: #d87332;
			}

			.milestone-card.talents {
				border-color: var(--amber);
			}

			.milestone-card.specs {
				border-color: var(--leaf-green);
			}

			/* Callout */
			.callout {
				background: var(--forest-dark);
				padding: 1.5rem;
				border-radius: 8px;
				border-left: 4px solid var(--amber);
				margin: 1.5rem 0;
				font-size: 1.05rem;
			}

			/* Example Box */
			.example-box {
				background: var(--forest-dark);
				padding: 1.5rem;
				border-radius: 8px;
				margin: 1.5rem 0;
				border: 2px solid var(--moss-green);
			}

			.example-box h4 {
				margin-top: 0;
			}

			/* Progression Pillars */
			.progression-pillars {
				display: grid;
				grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
				gap: 1.5rem;
				margin: 2rem 0;
			}

			.pillar {
				background: var(--forest-dark);
				padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
				border-radius: 12px;
				text-align: center;
				border: 2px solid var(--leaf-green);
				position: relative;
			}

			.pillar-number {
				display: inline-block;
				width: 40px;
				height: 40px;
				background: var(--amber);
				color: var(--forest-dark);
				border-radius: 50%;
				font-size: 1.5rem;
				font-weight: 900;
				line-height: 40px;
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
			}

			.pillar h3 {
				color: var(--amber);
				font-size: 1.2rem;
				margin: 0.5rem 0 0.75rem;
			}

			.pillar p {
				font-size: 0.95rem;
				color: var(--text-light);
			}

			/* Note */
			.note {
				font-style: italic;
				color: var(--leaf-green);
				font-size: 0.95rem;
				margin-top: 1rem;
			}

			/* Responsive */
			@media (max-width: 768px) {
				.nav .container {
					flex-direction: column;
					gap: 1rem;
				}

				.nav-links {
					gap: 1rem;
					flex-wrap: wrap;
					justify-content: center;
				}

				.page-header h1 {
					font-size: 2rem;
				}

				.rule-section {
					padding: 1.5rem;
				}

				.progression-table th,
				.progression-table td,
				.proficiency-table th,
				.proficiency-table td {
					padding: 0.75rem;
					font-size: 0.9rem;
				}

				.milestone-grid,
				.progression-pillars {
					grid-template-columns: 1fr;
				}
			}

			/* Smooth Scrolling */
			html {
				scroll-behavior: smooth;
			}
		</style>
	</body>
</html>
